\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 The first person was an accident. Their existence, arbitrary, invented by a caprice of power.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 In an act of Granted them, first, primitive categories of thought. These attained, he granted them the gift of abstract thought- to see a rock, but think of a hammer, or a spear point, or a grinding stone. That he did not anticipate, purpose for the abstract things that he had not created. To think of a thought, but instead see a deeper thought, to feel a feeling,and then wonder instead about choice.}}